            <div class="row" id="permitTypeRow">
              <a name="permittypes"></a>
              <h2 class="blue-heading-bar">Permit Information</h2>
              <div class="table-responsive">
                <div class="row">
                  <div class="table featureBoxes-2col">
                    <div class="featureBox col-sm-6">
                      <h3 class="title">Permits</h3>
                      <p class="text">
                        The Commercial Transport Procedures Manual provides direction on policy, links to regulations, and clarification on T-Forms.
                        <p>
                          <a class="btn btn-default" href="http://www2.gov.bc.ca/gov/content?id=9E648C4DF75E4E62914AD07CAA1D27F5" style="white-space: normal;"
                            role="button" target="_blank">Commercial Transport Procedures</a>
                        </p>
                      </p>
                      <h3 class="title">Out of Province</h3>
                      <p class="text">
                        <p>Commercial drivers transporting loads across BC borders need to take into account intra-provincial
                          and cross-border issues, procedures, laws, regulations, and required permits.</p>
                        <p>
                          <a class="btn btn-default" href="http://www2.gov.bc.ca/gov/content?id=1C4DE7A63046419C982D061F245058C7" style="white-space: normal;"
                            role="button" target="_blank">Out of Province Transport</a>
                        </p>
                      </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="featureBox col-sm-6">
                      <h3 class="title">T-Forms</h3>
                      <p class="text">
                        Click on the link below to access T-Forms. Each T-Form provides further information regarding commodity, vehicle, and regional
                        limitations. T-Forms will be attached to your Permit. For those loads that do not require a permit
                        or fee (Parade Floats/War Canoes and Non Resident Exemption for Repairs) simply print out the T-Form, 
                        fill it out and send it to the PPC.
                        <p>
                          <a class="btn btn-default" href="http://www.cvse.ca/whatsnew.html?tab=t-forms" role="button" target="_blank">View the T-Forms</a>
                        </p>
                      </p>

                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
